<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 01:23:18 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>琵琶鱼以其内置的钓鱼竿而闻名。新研究揭示了这些诱饵如何在奇怪的生物中进化</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/anglerfish-are-known-for-their-built-in-fishing-rods-new-research-sheds-light-on-how-these-lures-evolved-in-the-strange-creatures-180988577/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，这种奇怪的附肢在大约 7200 万年前首次出现在鱼类的祖先身上。如今，雌性可能不仅用它们来吸引猎物，还用它们与潜在的配偶交流</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 21:41:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/anglerfish-are-known-for-their-built-in-fishing-rods-new-research-sheds-light-on-how-these-lures-evolved-in-the-strange-creatures-180988577/</guid></item><item><title>本周抬头即可看到天琴座流星雨的顶峰。 2700 年来，人类一直在记录这一令人眼花缭乱的年度展示</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/look-up-this-week-to-see-the-peak-of-the-lyrid-meteor-shower-humans-have-documented-this-dazzling-display-for-2700-years-180988578/</link><description>4 月 22 日凌晨，月落时间将为美国大部分地区的观星者在日出前提供一片漆黑的天空</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:48:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/look-up-this-week-to-see-the-peak-of-the-lyrid-meteor-shower-humans-have-documented-this-dazzling-display-for-2700-years-180988578/</guid></item><item><title>科学家在纽约公墓下发现了 560 万只穴居蜂。该集团是有记录以来最大的集团之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-found-5-6-million-burrowing-bees-beneath-a-cemetery-in-new-york-the-group-is-one-of-the-largest-on-record-180988573/</link><description>伊萨卡的研究人员估计了 2023 年春季从当地墓地出现的地面筑巢蜜蜂的数量，揭示了一些未被充分研究的传粉媒介的数量</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:12:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-found-5-6-million-burrowing-bees-beneath-a-cemetery-in-new-york-the-group-is-one-of-the-largest-on-record-180988573/</guid></item><item><title>泰坦尼克号载有 3500 件救生衣，但几乎全部都消失在历史之中。这件作品刚刚在拍卖会上以近 100 万美元的价格售出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-titanic-carried-3500-life-jackets-but-almost-all-of-them-have-been-lost-to-history-this-one-just-sold-at-auction-for-nearly-1-million-180988574/</link><description>这件文物属于头等舱乘客劳拉·梅贝尔·弗朗卡特利 (Laura Mabel Francatelli)，她是一名随雇主前往芝加哥的秘书。这是唯一一件出现在拍卖会上的与 1912 年海难幸存者有关的救生衣</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:11:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-titanic-carried-3500-life-jackets-but-almost-all-of-them-have-been-lost-to-history-this-one-just-sold-at-auction-for-nearly-1-million-180988574/</guid></item><item><title>科德角海岸附近的海盗沉船事件刷新了西非黄金的历史记录</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/pirate-shipwreck-off-the-coast-of-cape-cod-sets-the-historical-record-straight-on-west-african-gold-180988572/</link><description>欧洲人散布关于阿坎贸易伙伴黄金品质下降的谣言。对“Whydah Gally”沉船文物的新分析讲述了一个不同的故事</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 17:03:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/pirate-shipwreck-off-the-coast-of-cape-cod-sets-the-historical-record-straight-on-west-african-gold-180988572/</guid></item><item><title>最新研究表明，这些聪明的祖先可能和现代人类一样喜爱水晶</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/newly-discovered-stone-tools-made-from-geodes-and-fossils-hint-at-homo-erectus-connection-with-the-cosmos-180988565/</link><description>以色列考古学家出土了直立人用化石和水晶等石头制成的史前手斧，这也许是他们想要与宇宙联系的标志</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/newly-discovered-stone-tools-made-from-geodes-and-fossils-hint-at-homo-erectus-connection-with-the-cosmos-180988565/</guid></item><item><title>这座中世纪城堡坐落在史前时间胶囊的顶部。新的发掘可能揭示英国尼安德特人的历史</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-medieval-castle-sits-atop-a-prehistoric-time-capsule-new-excavations-could-reveal-the-history-of-neanderthals-in-britain-180988562/</link><description>在威尔士地标下方的一个洞穴中，考古学家发现了过去 12 万年来人类和动物来访的证据。现在，他们正在启动为期五年的挖掘项目</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-medieval-castle-sits-atop-a-prehistoric-time-capsule-new-excavations-could-reveal-the-history-of-neanderthals-in-britain-180988562/</guid></item><item><title>1996 年，辣妹组合永远改变了流行音乐。三十年后，她们的标志性服装在伦敦举办的新展览中展出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/spice-girls-changed-pop-forever-in-1996-thirty-years-later-their-iconic-outfits-are-on-display-in-a-new-exhibition-in-london-180988569/</link><description>巴比肯音乐图书馆正在通过一场演出来庆祝英国流行文化，其中包括 Mel B 的豹纹紧身衣、Emma Bunton 的蓝色连衣裙和 Geri Halliwell 的英国国旗靴子</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 12:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/spice-girls-changed-pop-forever-in-1996-thirty-years-later-their-iconic-outfits-are-on-display-in-a-new-exhibition-in-london-180988569/</guid></item><item><title>在困难时期，玛雅人拒绝了神圣的王权。这座新发现的公共建筑揭示了向共享电力的过渡是如何展开的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-times-trouble-maya-rejected-divine-kingship-newly-discovered-public-building-reveals-how-the-transition-to-shared-power-unfolded-180988567/</link><description>危地马拉北部的考古学家发现了一个带柱廊的开放式大厅，可能曾用作议会大厦，当地领导人和普通民众在这里会面讨论政治问题</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-times-trouble-maya-rejected-divine-kingship-newly-discovered-public-building-reveals-how-the-transition-to-shared-power-unfolded-180988567/</guid></item><item><title>科学家仍然不知道大峡谷是如何或何时形成的。新研究可能暗示其古老起源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-still-dont-know-how-or-when-the-grand-canyon-formed-new-research-may-hint-at-its-ancient-origins-180988570/</link><description>研究人员表示，大约 660 万年前，古老的科罗拉多河在亚利桑那州北部形成了一个古老的湖泊，该湖泊向西溢出，最终形成了大峡谷</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 19:11:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-still-dont-know-how-or-when-the-grand-canyon-formed-new-research-may-hint-at-its-ancient-origins-180988570/</guid></item><item><title>伦敦莎士比亚故居已消失在历史之中。一位学者在档案馆中发现了一张地图，显示了其确切位置</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/shakespeares-house-in-london-was-lost-to-history-a-scholar-discovered-a-map-in-the-archives-that-revealed-its-exact-location-180988566/</link><description>这位诗人在 1616 年去世前三年购买了这处房产。他是否希望在这座他创作最著名戏剧的城市度过更多时光？</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 18:46:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/shakespeares-house-in-london-was-lost-to-history-a-scholar-discovered-a-map-in-the-archives-that-revealed-its-exact-location-180988566/</guid></item><item><title>83 年前，第一次 LSD 旅行实际上是骑自行车。迷幻迷们每年 4 月 19 日都会庆祝这个节日</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-first-lsd-trip-was-a-literal-bicycle-ride-83-years-ago-fans-of-the-psychedelic-celebrate-the-occasion-every-april-19-180988564/</link><description>1943年，瑞士的一位化学家合成了一种改变意识的药物。他的发现改变了医学、精神病学和生物学的研究，并成为反主流文化运动的核心组成部分</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 17:56:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-first-lsd-trip-was-a-literal-bicycle-ride-83-years-ago-fans-of-the-psychedelic-celebrate-the-occasion-every-april-19-180988564/</guid></item><item><title>数百名西班牙定居者死于“饥荒港”。这枚新发现的银币揭示了 400 年前这个注定要灭亡的殖民地的建立地点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hundreds-of-spanish-settlers-died-at-the-port-of-famine-this-newly-discovered-silver-coin-reveals-where-the-doomed-colony-was-founded-400-years-ago-180988519/</link><description>费利佩国王城 (Ciudad del Rey Don Felipe) 于 1584 年在智利麦哲伦海峡北岸建立。几年后，当一位英国航海家发现它时，幸存者所剩无几。</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 17:42:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hundreds-of-spanish-settlers-died-at-the-port-of-famine-this-newly-discovered-silver-coin-reveals-where-the-doomed-colony-was-founded-400-years-ago-180988519/</guid></item><item><title>绕月飞行后，阿耳忒弥斯 2 号宇航员反思这次经历的重要性：“我们作为国家和人类做到了这一点”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-rounding-the-moon-artemis-2-astronauts-reflect-on-the-enormity-of-the-experience-we-as-countries-and-as-humans-did-this-180988568/</link><description>在从太空返回后的第一次新闻发布会上，四名宇航员描述了自己的渺小但与地球上的人们团结在一起的感觉，并表示这次任务是全人类的成就</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 15:01:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-rounding-the-moon-artemis-2-astronauts-reflect-on-the-enormity-of-the-experience-we-as-countries-and-as-humans-did-this-180988568/</guid></item><item><title>丰富的浆果收获让这些矮胖的濒临灭绝的鹦鹉心情愉悦。现在，科学家们正在庆祝育种繁荣</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-bountiful-berry-harvest-put-these-chunky-endangered-parrots-in-the-mood-now-scientists-are-celebrating-a-breeding-bonanza-180988510/</link><description>新西兰鸮鹦鹉已产下 256 枚蛋，其中约 100 枚已孵化，为长达数十年的保护工作提供了亮点。官方的雏鸟数量要到最小的雏鸟大约 5 个月大时才会得到确认</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-bountiful-berry-harvest-put-these-chunky-endangered-parrots-in-the-mood-now-scientists-are-celebrating-a-breeding-bonanza-180988510/</guid></item><item><title>为什么这座中世纪英国城堡下面埋有冷战时期的碉堡？如果发生核“世界末日”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-is-a-cold-war-bunker-buried-underneath-this-medieval-english-castle-in-case-of-nuclear-armageddon-180988561/</link><description>考古学家在斯卡伯勒城堡下方发现了 20 世纪冲突的遗迹，数十年后，地堡被封锁，其确切位置已被遗忘</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 19:00:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-is-a-cold-war-bunker-buried-underneath-this-medieval-english-castle-in-case-of-nuclear-armageddon-180988561/</guid></item><item><title>这些小蚂蚁在大蚂蚁身上爬行，然后把它们舔干净。科学家们不确定这种行为对他们有什么好处</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-tiny-ants-crawled-all-over-larger-ants-and-licked-them-clean-scientists-arent-sure-how-this-behavior-benefits-any-of-them-180988555/</link><description>在目睹了亚利桑那州沙漠中的相互作用后，史密森学会的一位研究人员表示，小蚂蚁会摘取美味佳肴，而大蚂蚁则会在难以到达的地方进行彻底的梳理。</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 18:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-tiny-ants-crawled-all-over-larger-ants-and-licked-them-clean-scientists-arent-sure-how-this-behavior-benefits-any-of-them-180988555/</guid></item><item><title>大型入侵啮齿动物正在加州造成严重破坏。新研究表明有人故意引入它们</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/large-invasive-rodents-are-wreaking-havoc-in-california-new-research-suggests-someone-deliberately-introduced-them-180988554/</link><description>基因测试显示，自 2017 年以来生活在加利福尼亚州的海狸鼠与俄勒冈州中部的海狸鼠种群关系最为密切——距离太远，这些生物无法自行迁徙</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 16:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/large-invasive-rodents-are-wreaking-havoc-in-california-new-research-suggests-someone-deliberately-introduced-them-180988554/</guid></item><item><title>20 世纪 90 年代，一只狗教孩子们了解莎士比亚和荷马。一部新纪录片讲述“叉骨”的故事——从他的后空翻到他的历史帽子</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-1990s-a-dog-taught-kids-about-shakespeare-and-homer-a-new-documentary-tells-the-tale-of-wishbone-from-his-backflips-to-his-historical-hats-180988552/</link><description>这部电影让演员和工作人员重聚，他们看到了杰克罗素梗犬在 PBS 上将经典文学带入生活的潜力</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 15:31:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-1990s-a-dog-taught-kids-about-shakespeare-and-homer-a-new-documentary-tells-the-tale-of-wishbone-from-his-backflips-to-his-historical-hats-180988552/</guid></item><item><title>中世纪的文字和树木年轮帮助研究人员追踪 800 年前的太阳风暴并重建过去的太阳周期</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/medieval-writings-and-tree-rings-helped-researchers-track-a-solar-storm-from-800-years-ago-and-reconstruct-past-solar-cycles-180988546/</link><description>日本诗人藤原帝家的日记以及来自亚洲和欧洲的其他历史资料在一项新研究中发挥了关键作用</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/medieval-writings-and-tree-rings-helped-researchers-track-a-solar-storm-from-800-years-ago-and-reconstruct-past-solar-cycles-180988546/</guid></item></channel></rss>